  "section_anchors": [
    {
      "text": "We present two systems contributions: a factored norm that decomposes the squared norm into base, cross, and Gram terms computable through O(dout r + r2) intermediates, eliminating the dense product",
      "expected_section": "Abstract",
      "position": "middle"
    },
    {
      "text": "Final-logit cosine similarity exceeds 0.9999 across all model/GPU pairs",
      "expected_section": "Abstract",
      "position": "end"
    },
    {
      "text": "The bottleneck is the row-wise L2 norm of the composed weight W + sBA",
      "expected_section": "Introduction",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "This paper does not propose a new adapter architecture, optimizer, or training recipe",
      "expected_section": "Introduction",
      "position": "middle"
    },
    {
      "text": "The row-wise squared norm of the composed weight expands into three terms",
      "expected_section": "Algebraic Decomposition",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "The magnitude division is always computed in PyTorch after the kernel returns",
      "expected_section": "Assembly and Precision",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "The dominant transient is the base-norm computation",
      "expected_section": "Complexity",
      "position": "middle"
    },
    {
      "text": "The fused Triton kernel collapses these into a single pass",
      "expected_section": "Compose Kernel",
      "position": "middle"
    },
    {
      "text": "The fused backward computes dlora and dbase in a single Triton pass",
      "expected_section": "Backward Kernel",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "A second Triton kernel fuses Equation 5, computing wnorm from the three factored terms",
      "expected_section": "Norm Assembly Kernel",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "The composition path is selected at runtime by _compose_with_dispatch",
      "expected_section": "Runtime Dispatch",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Microbenchmarks use six GPUs spanning four architecture generations",
      "expected_section": "Setup",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Table 4 summarizes the headline result: gradient-computation speedup across six 8-32B VLMs on three GPUs",
      "expected_section": "Model-Level Performance",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "The factored norm is particularly valuable when training and inference compete for GPU memory",
      "expected_section": "Deployment Context",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Where fusion offers no advantage",
      "expected_section": "Tradeoffs and Limitations",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Parameter-efficient fine-tuning. LoRA introduced low-rank adapter decomposition; DoRA adds magnitude-direction separation",
      "expected_section": "Related Work",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We presented a systems implementation of DoRA: a factored norm that reduces working memory",
      "expected_section": "Conclusion",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "All source code, benchmark scripts, raw JSON results, Triton autotune caches, and figure generation scripts are available",
      "expected_section": "Data Availability",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "This work was developed through extensive collaborative programming with Claude Opus 4.6",
      "expected_section": "Acknowledgements",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Formal contract for clean-room replication",
      "expected_section": "Forward Contract and Execution Semantics",
      "position": "end"
    },
    {
      "text": "Chunk alignment. The chunk size aligns to 64 elements on CUDA/XPU devices",
      "expected_section": "Implementation Details",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "This appendix provides exact specifications for the three Triton kernels and the PyTorch magnitude division stage",
      "expected_section": "Kernel Specifications",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Code and data. All source code, benchmark scripts, raw JSON results, Triton autotune caches",
      "expected_section": "Reproducibility",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Table 13 extends the main-body memory comparison to all six models",
      "expected_section": "Full Model-Level Memory Table",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "The following figures show single-layer end-to-end speedup, which isolates the per-layer overhead but does not predict model-level speedup",
      "expected_section": "Single-Layer E2E Decomposition",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Table 15 summarizes the DoRA norm implementation across five major fine-tuning frameworks",
      "expected_section": "Framework Survey",
      "position": "start"
    }
  ],
